trip_comments: Princess Cruise San Francisco to Alaska round trip, Day 2 northbound. Wind SW 6 kt; Overcast, Air temp 55F; SST 53.6F; Swell 3-5 ft NW.  Paul Lehman (with 9-person Wings tour group) and Bruce Rideout observers. MUPE seen first by Paul Lehman, then by Bruce Rideout and others in the group. An all-dark petrel with long narrow wings cocked forward at the carpi, long glides and steep arcs. Although they can have pale primary bases below, I could not discern any paleness on the underwing. The time was 07:35 and the coordinates 41.52209, -125.58444.

trip_comments: San Bernardino Valley Audubon pelagic trip out of Dana Point aboard the Ocean Institute's R/V Sea Explorer, with Mike Bursk as Captain and Tom Benson, Jon Feenstra, Matt Grube, Robert McNab, and Brad Singer as leaders. From Dana Point Harbor, we traveled west to Lausen Sea Mount, north-northwest to Platforms Eureka, Ellen, and Edith, east and south to San Gabriel Canyon, east toward Laguna Beach, and finally southeast along the 100-fathom curve back to Dana Point Harbor, with minor variations in course for birds and ocean conditions. Weather was mostly cloudy but becoming partly cloudy midday, with light to moderate winds, and temperatures in the 60s (F). This checklist covers the area from Lausen Sea Mount to the halfway point to Platform Eureka, and includes several one mile transects along a chum and oil slick that we laid out over the sea mount.----

A windy, windy day; Elizabeth Ames, Matt Brady, Rebecca Green, Dan Maxwell and Jim Tietz observed.

Arrived at the island with Nick Lethaby at 1130 hrs via Island Packers for 3 days. ----Weather: High overcast conditions all day; calm on arrival with light breeze in the afternoon from the north. We arrived to find a significant number of migrants on the island.

Day 2 of 3 on the island. Many migrants present, fall-out conditions. With Nick Lethaby (NAL). ----Weather: High overcast in the AM, continuing through late afternoon. No moisture present on vegetation in the AM. ----100's of calling SWTH heard overhead in flight pre-dawn.
Very foggy in AM, clearing in early PM; Elizabeth Ames, Matt Brady, Dan Maxwell and Jim Tietz observed.

Clear skies and windy conditions caused most of our birds to leave. With Elizabeth Ames, Matt Brady, Mark Dettling, Megan Elrod, Dan Maxwell, and Pete Warzybok observing.

With Lucas Gaede (LCG) and Wes Fritz (WTF). Nick Lethaby (NAL) and Wes had been present since 10/19 and had highlights such as Black-throated Blue Warbler, Yellow-throated Warbler, Red Crossbill, Summer Tanager, Indigo Bunting and Long-eared Owl. Of this group of birds, only the Indigo Bunting remained through 10/21. Nick departed on the Islander around noon and Lucas, Wes and I stayed until 10/23.----This list 10/21 only. Overcast conditions in the AM continued into the afternoon. Light NW wind.
